<TEXT>
<P>
 Second Trial Ahead in Bar Study Case: A federal district court jury deadlocked 
on the punitive damages portion of an antitrust lawsuit brought by Barpassers 
of Santa Monica against BAR/BRI, the nation's largest bar review company.Last 
week, the jury awarded Barpassers nearly $4 million in damages, plus attorney 
fees. However, BAR/BRI was also awarded $752,000 in damages for deceptive 
advertising by Barpassers in the dispute between the rivals. A date for the 
retrial has not yet been set. 
