<HEADLINE>
<P>
VISA, SPRINT TEAM UP FOR DISCOUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Visa International stepped up its battle with MasterCard International on 
Wednesday by offering a new service with Sprint that lets users charge 
long-distance calls at a deep discount. 
</P>
<P>
 The Visa-Sprint alliance puts one more contender into a credit card industry 
already crowded with programs offering discounts for calls charged to their 
cards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Visa card's new feature, VisaPhone, ups the ante by offering a discount 
25% cheaper than the calling card rate offered by AT&T, the biggest 
long-distance carrier. 
</P>
<P>
 AT&T has been in a competitive brawl with Sprint and the other leading 
long-distance company, MCI. With VisaPhone, even users of AT&T's own Visa card, 
the Universal Card, could choose to receive the Sprint discount. 
</P>
