BRIEFLY: VETERANS AFFAIRS: ASSISTANCE PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs' West Los Angeles Medical Center has 
joined forces with the Salvation Army to create an emergency services program 
for homeless veterans. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, called HAVEN (Helping Assist Veterans with Emergency Needs), was 
dedicated on Tuesday by Veterans Affairs Secretary Jesse Brown. It is intended 
to provide temporary housing for homeless veterans and help them become 
self-sufficient. 
</P>
<P>
 "Men and women who fought for freedom should not have to live on the streets," 
Brown said in a statement issued Tuesday. "I consider this an absolute 
priority." 
</P>
