<P>
BUSINESS; FOOTBALL STAR OPENS RETAIL STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOE DONNELLY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The "Nigerian Nightmare" is making a comeback in retail. 
</P>
<P>
 Christian Okoye, the NFL's leading rusher in 1989, opened Christian Okoye 
Sports in Asuza recently.The former Kansas City Chiefs running back, nicknamed 
the Nigerian Nightmare in honor of his African homeland and his bruising 
running style, said he had always dreamed of opening an apparel store.  
</P>
<P>
 Okoye, who came to Azusa Pacific University from Nigeria on a track 
scholarship in 1982, reflected upon his decision to locate the store near his 
old haunts: "This area is growing. I thought it was a good location. I've 
always wanted to open a sports apparel store and I thought it would be nice to 
open it so close to my old school." 
</P>
<P>
 His brother, Emmanuel Okoye, said Okoye Sports will sell officially licensed 
sports apparel and merchandise. The store will not carry sporting equipment. 
</P>
<P>
 Christian Okoye missed last season with knee problems. He also recently 
underwent back surgery. Emmanuel Okoye said his brother is fully recovered and 
working out in hopes of joining an NFL team. 
</P>
