<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: VENICE; VISITORS MAY DASH TO BEACH THIS SUMMER ON BUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Venice Beach visitors can use a shuttle bus this summer to avoid crowded 
parking near the popular tourist spot. 
</P>
<P>
 The free summer bus service, which was introduced last year and this season 
will run from May 28 to Sept. 6, means beach-goers can park in a lot in Marina 
del Rey and ride to the beach on a DASH bus. Parking at the Marina Business 
Center, at 4501 Glencoe Ave., costs $2.50. 
</P>
</TEXT>
