<P>
BEHIND THE SCENES; GREEK IS THE WORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 They savored souvlakia, sipped ouzo and danced to the sounds of a bouzuki at 
the Greek Festival at St. John the Baptist Greek Orthodox Church in Anaheim 
Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Showing off the best of the Aegean Sea included a colorful display of national 
costumes. 
</P>
<P>
 Folk dancers performed outside the Byzantine church wearing beaded hats, 
braided vests, pleated kilts and other items that represented some of the 
country's traditional dress, which varies from region to region. 
</P>
<P>
 Fine embroidery, silver jewelry, woven fabrics and other handicrafts of Greece 
were spotted on guests as well. 
