<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CANTU BOWS OUT; BROWNE TO COACH BASEBALL AT ALEMANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Frank Cantu, who was hired earlier this month to succeed Jim Ozella as Alemany 
High baseball coach, has withdrawn from the position and been replaced by 
assistant coach Tim Browne. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany Athletic Director Dudley Rooney said Cantu realized that coaching 
would conflict with his duties as principal at St. Didacus, an elementary 
school in Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 Browne, a 10-year assistant under Ozella and a math teacher at Alemany, will 
take over the program next season. 
</P>
<P>
 "It should be an easy transition," Rooney said. "All the kids know him and he 
obviously knows the program because he's been around a long time." 
</P>
<P>
 Catcher Eric Gillespie of Cal State Northridge has been named to the NCAA 
Division I freshman All-American baseball team, sponsored by Mizuno and 
Collegiate Baseball magazine. 
</P>
<P>
 Gillespie led the team with 80 hits and a .342 average. 
</P>
<P>
 Jacob Cruz of Arizona State was named a second-team All-American by Collegiate 
Baseball. Cruz, a junior from Channel Islands High, batted .412 with 12 home 
runs and 61 runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus High shortstop Danny Cato and pitchers Steve Rogers and John Maggiora 
have committed to attend The Master's College. The school also received a 
commitment Doug Maggiora, John's brother, a former Saugus and College of the 
Canyons pitcher who will transfer from Nichols State in Louisiana. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Johnson, an 11-year sophomore and junior varsity basketball coach at 
Simi Valley High, has been named varsity coach at Newbury Park, replacing Paul 
Coffman, who resigned after one season. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson, 34, a 1978 graduate of Newbury Park, led the Simi Valley sophomore 
and junior varsity teams to a total of eight Marmonte League titles. Track and 
Field 
</P>
<P>
 Corri Moore of Spring Valley Monte Vista High and Jere Miller of San Diego 
Patrick Henry have signed letters of intent with Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Moore has a personal best of 23 feet 8 inches in the long jump and Miller has 
run 21.46 seconds in the 200 meters and 48.11 in the 400. Golf 
</P>
<P>
 Jennifer Francoeur, a three-year starter on the Kennedy High golf team, has 
signed with Montevallo, an NAIA school in Alabama. Francoeur, who will receive 
a partial scholarship, carries a seven handicap and is the first Kennedy girl 
to receive a golf scholarship. Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 Gene Urcan, a part-time starter for the Cal State Northridge volleyball team 
at the start of last season, said he is transferring to San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
 Urcan, a 6-foot-5 former Chatsworth High star, left Northridge at mid-season. 
</P>
<P>
 He cited philosophical differences with Coach John Price. Field Hockey 
</P>
<P>
 The California Cup, an annual international field hockey tournament that 
attracts more than 1,000 players, is scheduled for this weekend at Moorpark 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-day event is the 23rd since the tournament's inception in 1971.  
</P>
<P>
 Play will begin Saturday and culminate with championship matches all day 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. Junior National Team, which includes several players from Ventura 
County, also will compete in the tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
