EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; DEADLINE FRIDAY FOR 2 CITY COMMISSIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Friday is the deadline to apply for two Simi Valley commissions. 
</P>
<P>
 The Citizens Election Advisory Commission is seeking one regular and two 
alternate members to serve on the commission. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission serves as a five-member advisory board to the City Council, 
reviewing candidate and committee financial campaign statements and advising 
candidates of election code requirements. 
</P>
<P>
 Any Simi Valley resident not working for the city or affiliated with a 
campaign may apply. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are due at 5 p.m. Friday. For more information, call City Hall at 
583-6720. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents who are 60 years of age or older may apply for an open seat on the 
Simi Valley Council on Aging. The council meets monthly to discuss issues 
affecting senior citizens, including nutrition, housing, transportation and 
education. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are due at 5 p.m. Friday. For more information, call the Senior 
Services Center at 526-9237. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
