</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities on Wednesday continued to search for a 27-year-old man who 
wandered away from Camarillo State Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Tipton is deaf, developmentally disabled and cannot communicate, said 
Myron Dimmett, spokesman for Camarillo State Hospital.Hospital officials say he 
is not considered a threat to the public. 
</P>
<P>
 Staff members discovered Tipton missing about 8 p.m. Sunday, Dimmett said. He 
had been playing baseball with several other patients. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're not sure how he got out," Dimmett said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tipton escaped once a few years ago, but was found quickly, Dimmett said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County Sheriff's Search and Rescue Team and hospital staff members 
searched unsuccessfully for Tipton along Potrero Road and Las Posas Road on 
Wednesday, Dimmett said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tipton was last seen wearing a gray sweat shirt and gray pants. He is 5-foot-5 
and weighs about 155 pounds. He has brown hair and brown eyes. PEGGY Y. LEE 
