Barbara Kruger, Louise Lawler, Richard Prince and 32 others. At the Laguna Art 
Museum. * Through Aug. 14: "Ancient Nubia: Egypt's Rival in Africa" -- 
organized by the University Museum, University of Pennsylvania -- examines a 
sophisticated ancient Nile River Valley civilization that flourished between 
3100 BC and AD 400. With 300 artifacts, including statuary, ceramic vessels, 
jewelry and funerary inscriptions. At the Bowers Museum of Cultural Art. * 
Through Sept. 15: 'Artists Abroad" features paintings of foreign parts by 
artists who eventually came to California and worked in an 
