<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five-year T-Note Yields Up: Yields on the Treasury notes rose to the highest 
level in more than two years.The high yield was 6.78%, up from 6.6% at the last 
auction April 28. It was the highest rate since five-year notes sold for 6.93% 
on April 23, 1992. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 6.75%, with 
each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,987.50. A total of $11 billion in 
notes were sold out of bids totaling $31.6 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
