</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brooks Bros. to Add 20 Stores: The nation's largest retailer of traditional, 
upscale men's and women's clothing said it will open the stores, 10 of them 
factory outlets, in the United States this year. William Roberti, president and 
chief executive, also said Brooks Bros. will renovate or relocate 10 other U.S. 
stores and open three or four stores in Japan this year. There are 133 Brooks 
Bros. stores worldwide, including 57 stores and 26 outlets in the United 
States. 
