<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; MAN SHOOTS HIMSELF ACCIDENTALLY, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 23-year-old man who was trying to prevent a shooting mishap died late 
Tuesday after shooting himself in the head accidentally, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Gonzalez, who lived in the 1900 block of West Martha Lane, had taken the 
gun away from a relative to avoid an accident and had checked it to make sure 
it was not loaded, Santa Ana police spokesman Sgt. Dick Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 Faust said Gonzalez mistakenly believed the gun was not loaded when he pulled 
back on its slide and no rounds were ejected. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez then playfully put the gun to his head and pulled the trigger, Faust 
said. The gun fired. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics from the Santa Ana Fire Department took Gonzalez to UCI Medical 
Center in Orange, where he was pronounced dead at 11:13 p.m., Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez was an employee of Baxter Healthcare Corp., according to family 
members. 
</P>
<P>
 A rosary will be recited at 7 tonight at Brown's Mortuary in Santa Ana. 
Funeral services are planned for 10 a.m. Friday at Immaculate Heart of Mary 
Church in Santa Ana. ACCIDENTAL DEATH 
</P>
</TEXT>
