<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Visa, Sprint Team Up for Discount: Visa International stepped up its battle 
with MasterCard International on Wednesday by offering a new service with 
Sprint that lets users charge long-distance calls at a deep discount.The 
Visa-Sprint alliance puts one more contender into an industry already crowded 
with programs offering discounts for calls charged to their cards. The Visa 
card's new feature, VisaPhone, ups the ante by offering a discount 25% cheaper 
than the calling card rate offered by AT&T, the biggest long-distance carrier. 
AT&T has been in a competitive brawl with Sprint and MCI. With VisaPhone, even 
users of AT&T's own Visa card, the Universal Card, could receive the Sprint 
discount. 
