<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECT IN U.S. ENVOY'S DEATH FOUND IN BEIRUT JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lebanese authorities hunting the killers of a U.S. ambassador murdered in 
Beirut during the 1975-90 civil war finally found one of the suspects -- in a 
Beirut jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Bassem Mohammed Farkh is serving a sentence for heroin dealing, handed down in 
March. 
</P>
<P>
 Farkh is one of three suspects in the 1976 murder of U.S. Ambassador Francis 
E. Meloy, economic counselor Robert O. Waring and their Lebanese driver. 
