<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LAWNDALE; COUNCIL PASSES MEASURES TO THWART NEPOTISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Lawndale City Council approved two measures last week to prevent nepotism 
at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members voted unanimously in favor of a law that prohibits the city 
from hiring relatives of top city employees and elected or appointed officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance also would bar relatives from working in the same department 
under certain circumstances. Current employees would not be affected as long as 
they remain in their present positions. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the council voted 3 to 2 to bar the appointment of relatives to 
committees. Mayor Harold E. Hofmann and Councilman Larry Rudolph voted against 
the new policy. They said the measure was aimed at Rudolph's wife, a parks and 
recreation commissioner. 
</P>
<P>
 Shirley Rudolph was first appointed by Hofmann 12 years ago, four years before 
Councilman Rudolph was elected. SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
