<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; TAXES: ELDERLY MAY QUALIFY FOR REBATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Elderly and disabled residents may be eligible for a rebate from the Franchise 
Tax Board. 
</P>
<P>
 Through the state's Volunteer Tax Assistance Program, individuals with income 
of less than $13,200 can get a rebate of up to $240. 
</P>
<P>
 Homeowners can get the rebate based on their income level and the amount of 
property tax they pay, but they also must make less than $13,200.  
</P>
<P>
 Last year more than 160,000 seniors and disabled people statewide got money 
back through the program. 
</P>
<P>
 In Carson, state-trained volunteers will help to determine eligibility and to 
fill out forms. For more information, call Carson Senior Services at (310) 
952-1775. MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
