<P>
BRIEFLY; TRAFFIC: CONSTRUCTION OF WHEELCHAIR RAMPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Traffic lanes in several streets in Torrance, Rolling Hills and San Pedro will 
be reduced or closed next month when construction starts on wheelchair ramps. 
</P>
<P>
 Del Amo Boulevard westbound and Hamilton Avenue northbound will be reduced to 
one lane and the left-hand turn lanes during working hours, said Donna 
Guyovich, spokeswoman for the county Public Works Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Bandini Street in San Pedro will be reduced to one lane in each direction, 
Guyovich said. 
</P>
<P>
 Work on Del Amo Boulevard eastbound, Hamilton Avenue southbound, and 1st, 2nd, 
3rd, 6th, and 7th streets in San Pedro is not expected to affect traffic flow. 
</P>
<P>
 Putting in the ramps is expected to be completed in June or July and cost 
about $59,000, Guyovich said. SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
