METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VENICE; MAN PARKED 
OUTSIDE LIQUOR STORE IS SHOT TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police on Wednesday were investigating the fatal shooting of a man in the 
Venice community of Oakwood, the second shooting in the area in the last four 
days. 
</P>
<P>
 Harold McDaniel, a 33-year-old Venice resident, was sitting in his car outside 
a liquor store about 6 p.m. Tuesday when he was approached by two men, one of 
whom fired several rounds, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said McDaniel was hit in the torso and died at the scene. One of the 
assailants was wearing a bandanna over his face and the other was wearing a ski 
cap, police said. Both fled in a yellow Chevrolet Impala. 
</P>
<P>
 "No warning or comments were given before the shooting," said Los Angeles 
Police Detective Mike DePasquale. Police said no suspects have been taken into 
custody and the case remains under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday morning, 22-year-old Juan Ramiro was shot outside his Venice 
residence. He remains in fair condition and is awaiting surgery for a gunshot 
wound to his arm. Authorities, who have made no arrests in the case, declined 
to identify the hospital where he is being treated, citing safety concerns. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither of the two gunshot victims was a gang member, police said. 
</P>
