<HEADLINE>
<P>
BY DESIGN; WITH STRINGS ATTACHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAUREEN SAJBEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Air, water and a piece of string. That's about all you'll need this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 Anything tied up or down -- or made entirely of deja vu macrame -- tops the 
list of warm-weather essentials. 
</P>
<P>
 Drawstring pants, apron dresses, skimpy club clothes, ventilated crochet tops 
and countless variations on the sneaker take the theme to heart. Even dress-up 
pumps with spike heels lace up the instep. And in the handbag department, the 
big thing is the "wallet on a string" -- a tiny purse with room for nothing 
more than a lipstick and a credit card. 
</P>
<P>
 Swimwear season brings back the itsy-bitsy string bikini, with triangle-shaped 
bras and bottoms. As with most retro trends, if you did it on the first 
go-round in the '70s, you're probably better off skipping it this time. The 
1994 incarnation is meant for skinny young things. MAUREEN SAJBEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
