<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: LONG BEACH; FINANCES CAUSE CLOSURE OF ACTIVIST COFFEEHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EMILY ADAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The coffeehouse that helped start a mini-revolt against the city's strict 
entertainment licensing laws for alcohol-free establishments has gone out of 
business. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniel Pinn, owner of the Habitat coffeehouse on 7th Street, said he was 
forced to close this month after losing money steadily since opening the small 
storefront shop in December. "I'm through with the coffeehouse thing," Pinn 
said. "There's no money in it." EMILY ADAMS 
</P>
