<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: FREE DISPOSAL OFFERED FOR HAZARDOUS WASTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents can dispose of used motor oil, paints, cleaners, pesticides, car 
batteries and other household hazardous waste for free at Veterans Stadium, 
5000 Lew Davis St., from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. June 4. 
</P>
<P>
 Because such waste can pollute ground and ocean water, disposing of it in 
trash cans, sewers and storm drains is illegal, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 There is no limit to how much waste will be accepted, as long as it comes from 
residents' households. No waste generated by businesses will be accepted. 
</P>
<P>
 The roundup is sponsored by the Los Angeles County Department of Public Works 
and the County Sanitation Districts. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call: (800) 552-5218 or (310) 908-4286. 
</P>
